  52 => '{"id":0,"warning":"","type":"addonsMustHave","name":"lgcookieslaw","version":"2.1.4","tab":"administration","displayName":"EU Cookie Law GDPR (Banner + Blocker)","description":"Updated module to fully comply with the regulations regarding cookies de 2022. It allows you to block cookies until you obtain the consent of the user who accesses your website","description_full":"Updated module to fully comply with the regulations regarding cookies de 2022. It allows you to block cookies until you obtain the consent of the user who accesses your website. And the possibility of selecting the type of cookies to install.","author":"L\\u00ednea Gr\\u00e1fica","limited_countries":[],"parent_class":"","onclick_option":false,"is_configurable":0,"need_instance":0,"not_on_disk":1,"available_on_addons":1,"trusted":1,"active":0,"additional_description":"It now allows you to include groups of cookies by purpose, so that cookies can be grouped according to their purpose and the end user can accept only those they need. Using the configurator options you can change the name and description of the purpose.*Important: the groups of technical cookies must be accepted.By default, 5 groups have been included:Functional (technical)AdvertisingAnalyticalPerformanceOther cookies\\u00a0Updated module to fully comply with the Marzo 2021 cookie regulations. It allows you to block cookies until you obtain the consent of the user accessing your website. And the possibility to select the type of cookies to be installed among functional and third party ones.Our module fully complies with the European Law on Cookies, the LOPD and the directives of the LSSI and guarantees you complete protection. Updated to comply with the latest modifications of the RGPD.Full compliance with the European Law on Cookies (last modifications of the RGPD \\u2013 Update 2021)New customisable informative responsive configuration banner.In addition to inserting a warning banner, it is the only module that allows third party modules that use cookies to be blocked until the user gives his consent.Furthermore, it gives you the option of customising the module to comply 100% with the\\u00a0new requirements of the RGPD\\u00a0(European Union). Our Cookies module complies with the\\u00a0Right of Rectification, with it users can delete the cookies installed from the site simply by accessing a url or even from their own customer profile.\\u00a0Obtaining consentThe user has to click on the \\u201cI accept\\u201d button in the warning banner to give his consent. As soon as the client gives his consent, the warning banner disappears and all the modules that use cookies will be activated and will work as usual. The user can configure the type of cookies to which he or she wants to give consent by clicking on the \\u2018Manage Cookies\\u2019 button and selecting which cookies he or she wants to activate or not.Blocking CookiesThe module allows the blocking of cookies until the user gives his consent. Cookies can be functional (mandatory) or from third parties. They allow the user to give his or her consent separately. This complies with the law as it differentiates the different types of cookies that the client accepts.Functional (mandatory) cookies:\\u00a0includes the key cookies for the operation of the website. For example, save the login data, the shopping cart, etc.Third-party cookies:\\u00a0includes cookies that collect data for tracking, segmentation, analysis, etc.In order to comply with the directives of the LSSI, we recommend that you deactivate the tracking modules (such as Google Analytics), social network modules (Facebook\\u2019s \\u201cLike\\u201d button, Google\\u2019s \\u201c+1\\u201d button, etc.) and targeted advertising. Please note that the modules required for the proper functioning of your shop (e.g. shopping basket cookie, session cookie\\u2026) do not require prior consent.L\\u00ednea Gr\\u00e1fica will in no case be responsible for any damage or harm caused by activating options which do not comply with the RGPD. The user is responsible for the legal texts which indicate the purpose of third party cookies. Please note that the user\\/owner of the e-commerce where the module is installed is solely responsible for the legal texts to be introduced, such as the notice and explanation of the purpose of third party cookies. Linea Grafica will in no case be responsible for any damage or harm that may be caused by activating options that do not comply with the RGPD.\\u00a0Revocation of consentIn compliance with the law, the user may revoke their consent at any time. As soon as they withdraw their consent, the installed cookies are eliminated and consent is requested again.\\u00a0Banner content and customizationTo comply with the LSSI, the module allows you to customize the message that appears in the warning banner (to inform about the cookies used and their purpose) and add a \\u201cMore information\\u201d button to the banner that takes the user to a CMS page of your website (to explain in detail the use of cookies in your store).The notice banner is responsive and always occupies the entire width of the window. The module includes a Wysiwyg editor that allows you to fully customize the content of the banner (font, color, effects, html code \\u2026). You can also choose from the configuration page the background color of the banner, its opacity percentage (transparency) and its position (above or below the screen). In addition, the module is multi-language and automatically detects all the languages of your store, which allows you to write a different message per language.Information: we have developed the module so that it does not appear when search engine robots crawl your website and that it does not affect your SEO.\\u00a0Block screen until cookies are acceptedTo help the online shop lose as little information as possible it has an option that does not allow the customer to browse until they accept the cookie policy, i.e. it blocks the screen until the user accepts the cookies.\\u00a0Notice in the form of a pop upThe module displays a pop up to inform your customers about the use of cookies and ask for their consent for their installation.\\u00a0Multi-store modeThe module is compatible with multi-store mode and allows you to put the same warning banner in each of your stores, but the consent is the same for all your stores. If you accept cookies for one of your stores, the module will consider that you have accepted cookies for all your stores (indicate this in the Cookies Policy) and the warning banner will not appear later in the other stores.","compatibility":{"from":"1.6.0.4","to":"8.0.1"},"nb_rates":null,"avg_rate":null,"badges":{"badge":"https:\\/\\/medias2.prestastore.com\\/themes\\/prestastore\\/img\\/front\\/sprites\\/badges\\/module-editor.png"},"url":{"0":"https:\\/\\/addons.prestashop.com\\/ru\\/legal\\/8734-eu-cookie-law-gdpr-banner-blocker.html?utm_source=back-office&utm_medium=push-addons&utm_campaign=back-office-RU&utm_content=download"},"image":"..\\/img\\/tmp\\/ad00444082a2d960ac4c07f7cf731ac2.jpg","addons_buy_url":"https:\\/\\/addons.prestashop.com\\/ru\\/legal\\/8734-eu-cookie-law-gdpr-banner-blocker.html?utm_source=back-office&utm_medium=push-addons&utm_campaign=back-office-RU&utm_content=download","installed":false,"database_version":0,"interest":0}',
